          <msContents>
            <summary>Praise of the Hindu deity Śiva through a set of more than a 100 names rather than the 1000 names suggested by the title (sahasranāma); employed in private and public forms of worship (pūjā), using mantras. Presented as a discussion between the deity Kṛṣṇa and the legendary figures Mārkaṇḍeya and Vyāsa. Taken from the Śaṅkarasaṃhitā in the last section (uttarakhaṇḍa) of the Padmapurāṇa.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Śivasahasranāmastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">शिवसहस्रनामस्तोत्र</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīpadmapurāṇe uttarakhaṃḍe śaṃkarasaṃhitāyāṃ śrī kṛṣṇamārkaṃḍeyasaṃvāde vedasārākhye śivasahasranāmastotrasaṃpūrṇam // cha // cha // om ̐namaḥ śivāyaḥ // (f. 40v-41r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
